Harold's voice boomed from the counter. "Ash. Right on time. Coffee's fresh." Pot steamed on the warmer. Black sludge swirled. Mug chipped at the rim. Ash grabbed it. Steam curled hot. Sipped slow. Bitter edge bit the tongue. "Morning, boss. World still spinning?" Grin pulled tight. Harold snorted. Papers shuffled under his elbows. Glasses perched low on his nose.

"Spinning right into the ground." Harold tapped a stack. Ink smudged fresh signatures. Eyes darted to the window. Empty lot stretched out. No customers yet. Ash leaned on the broom handle. Bristles scraped tile. "Heard whispers. Corporate vultures circling?" Harold nodded. Tie knot pulled loose already. Belly shifted with a sigh.

