Ash set the mug down. Porcelain clinked. Steam wisped away. "Attic. Joy." He grabbed the keys from the hook. Metal scratched cold. Headed to the back. Storeroom door groaned open. Hinges whined protest. Stairs climbed narrow into the dark. Bulb swung overhead. Light swayed yellow. Shadows danced on beams. Cardboard towers loomed. Boxes sealed with yellowing tape.

