One box resisted. Tape stubborn. Ash wedged the blade deeper. Wood splintered faint. Inside, tapes nested tight. VHS spines cracked. Titles blurred. *Infinite Rental*. No date. No studio mark. He lifted it slow. Dust sifted down. Collar itched. Plastic case cool against his skin. Memories flickered. Late shifts. Rewinds in the glow.

Footsteps echoed below. Harold called up. "Lunch rush incoming. Clock it." Ash sealed the box. Tape ripped loud. Carried the load down. Stairs creaked under the bulk. Storeroom floor cluttered now. Crates shoved aside. He wiped his hands on pants. Streaks smeared dark. Clock hands inched past noon. Bell jingled. Door swung.

Customers trickled in. Umbrellas dripped. Plastic rustled. A kid tugged his mom's sleeve. Pointed at the action aisle. *Avengers*. Bright cover gleamed. Mom scanned shelves. Brows furrowed. "Pick quick. Rain's letting up." Voice clipped. Ash swept near the register. Bristles gathered grit. Ketchup packet burst under a heel. Red oozed across tile. Mop waited in the corner.

Harold rang up sales. Beeps pierced the hum. Receipts spat long. "That all?" Voice routine. Customer nodded. Bag crinkled. Door chime followed. Ash dipped the mop. Bucket sloshed gray. Swirled the spill. Fibers absorbed slow. Red faded to pink. He straightened. Back twinged. Years of bends caught up.

Afternoon dragged. Sun clawed through clouds. Light slanted sharp. Ash restocked the counter. Candy bars aligned neat. Gum packs fanned out. Fingers sticky from wrappers. Harold leaned close. Breath mint sharp. "Papers hit the news this morning. Local spot closing. Nostalgia bait." Ash nodded. Rag twisted in his fist. "Yeah. Read it on the break. 'End of an era.' Dramatic much?"

Harold chuckled. Gut shook. "You bet. One more week. Tops." He glanced at the clock. Hands ticked steady. Ash pocketed a stray receipt. Crumpled paper scratched. "Last dance, then. I'll take the finale shift." Words slipped out. Resolve settled. Harold clapped his shoulder. Weight lingered. "Knew I could count on you. Pay's bumped for the hassle."

Crowd thinned. Lunch stragglers cleared. Aisles emptied. Ash hauled the attic crates to the front. Stacked them neat. Labels faced out. Dust trails marked the path. He paused at the bathroom door. Mirror hung crooked. Frame chipped. Pushed it open. Faucet dripped steady. Sink gleamed under the bulb.

